In the name of the Father and of the Son

17:09.761 --> 17:11.827
and of the Holy Spirit,
bless us, O Lord,

17:11.891 --> 17:14.343
and these, thy gifts
which we are about to receive

17:14.432 --> 17:16.434
from thy bounty
through Jesus Christ, our Lord.

17:16.501 --> 17:18.223
In the name of the Father and of the Son

17:18.292 --> 17:20.378
- and the Holy Spirit, amen.
- Amen.

17:29.107 --> 17:31.209
What are you reading, Mrs. Raven?

17:31.583 --> 17:33.842
The journal of one
of the first priests here.

17:33.915 --> 17:35.810
I found it in your office.

17:36.121 --> 17:38.635
Well, if you have any
questions about church history,

17:38.690 --> 17:40.322
I'd be happy to help.

17:40.658 --> 17:43.697
Did you know this is not the first time
nature's come alive?

17:44.479 --> 17:46.865
Six people were killed
by wildlife here in Bridgeville

17:46.932 --> 17:48.700
on May 12th in 1860.

17:50.135 --> 17:51.546
Five more the next day.

17:51.703 --> 17:53.437
Three more the following.

17:53.531 --> 17:57.023
And you think this is related
to what we saw outside?

17:57.108 --> 17:59.311
Of course.
They called it the Black Spring.

17:59.377 --> 18:00.912
Natalie, I...

18:03.615 --> 18:05.291
You're looking for answers.

18:06.351 --> 18:08.685
We're all looking for answers.
It's human.

18:09.020 --> 18:12.787
But I beg you, look in the Bible.

18:13.568 --> 18:15.460
Your answers are there.

18:18.363 --> 18:20.727
Not just to this, to your pain as well.

18:23.983 --> 18:25.813
Why look f...

18:26.471 --> 18:29.007
Do you even know
what you're looking for?

18:43.722 --> 18:44.923
There it is.

18:47.432 --> 18:48.599
What?

18:51.096 --> 18:52.531
What I'm looking for.

18:52.769 --> 18:54.504
Ooh, that's a big one.

18:54.568 --> 18:56.434
- Oh, I got it.
- No!

19:05.710 --> 19:07.445
I found it.

19:11.016 --> 19:12.284
Thank you.

19:30.884 --> 19:32.452
Dinner is served.

19:34.955 --> 19:36.156
Thanks.

19:37.310 --> 19:39.980
I'm sorry about the gun.

19:45.232 --> 19:47.058
You see anyone else
when you were out there?

19:47.300 --> 19:49.379
We've been trying to find a car.
We can't find one that works.

19:49.551 --> 19:51.386
You haven't been out
in a while, have you?

19:51.731 --> 19:53.232
Cars stopped working.

19:53.314 --> 19:55.159
No, we drove through the mist
when we first got here.

19:55.267 --> 19:57.682
Yeah, but I was out
driving yesterday, looking.

19:57.904 --> 20:00.106
Couple people on the road
trying to get away, I guess.

20:00.154 --> 20:01.373
Then they just stopped

20:01.418 --> 20:03.988
at the same time, just like that.

20:04.203 --> 20:05.873
I've seen a couple working since then,

20:05.912 --> 20:07.613
but most of them just died.

20:07.680 --> 20:10.028
I got this from one
of those survivalist types.

20:10.103 --> 20:13.629
I wanted a family car,
but Toby thought it was so cool.

20:14.435 --> 20:17.715
Guy said he bought it because it
was a bug-out vehicle, you know,

20:17.757 --> 20:19.625
so old it didn't have a circuit board,

20:19.692 --> 20:22.597
in case aliens or whatever came
and fried our technology.

20:22.691 --> 20:24.559
I... I don't know anymore.

20:24.957 --> 20:27.862
I just know it's one
of the only ones that works.

20:28.745 --> 20:31.815
You should've seen how proud
Toby was riding in it.

20:37.877 --> 20:39.437
You know, Eve and I,

20:40.109 --> 20:41.570
we have a daughter.

20:42.648 --> 20:44.202
Her name is Alex.

20:44.517 --> 20:45.952
Where are they?

20:46.343 --> 20:48.364
They're at the mall.

20:48.788 --> 20:50.075
It's where I've been trying to go.

20:50.356 --> 20:52.358
I was hoping you could drive us.

20:54.026 --> 20:56.667
I... I wish I could, I really do,

20:56.721 --> 20:58.862
but I'm down to an eighth of a tank,

20:59.393 --> 21:02.300
and I'm gonna need every drop
to find my son.

21:05.964 --> 21:06.960
I'm sorry.

21:12.833 --> 21:14.816
Do me a favor,
and just sleep on it, all right?

21:55.609 --> 21:56.877
All right.

22:00.949 --> 22:02.849
"There once was an owl

22:02.916 --> 22:05.352
who said, 'What, ' and not, 'Who.'"

22:07.621 --> 22:09.222
You're sure about this, right?

22:09.465 --> 22:10.608
You prefer to keep listening

22:10.662 --> 22:12.155
to them bitching
about us being childish,

22:12.217 --> 22:14.227
or do you want to be a hero,

22:14.639 --> 22:17.532
and have Zoe be all, "Mmm,
you're my Mr. Strong Man.

22:17.579 --> 22:18.923
I want you so bad, Ted"?

22:18.977 --> 22:20.579
- Yo, stop it!
- "Oh, I want you, Ted.

22:20.618 --> 22:22.202
Your tiny, little arms
are turning me on."

22:22.269 --> 22:23.737
Okay. Okay.

22:23.804 --> 22:26.998
Besides, we don't have to go out there.

22:27.716 --> 22:29.678
Picked this up in sporting goods.

22:34.772 --> 22:37.207
Fucking boom.

22:37.757 --> 22:40.616
I mean, you're a sick bastard.

22:41.299 --> 22:42.300
Mm-hmm.

22:42.742 --> 22:43.943
Let's do this.

22:50.098 --> 22:52.137
We're sure this is safe, right?

22:52.265 --> 22:54.737
We served up two soldiers
in a shopping cart,

22:54.799 --> 22:56.269
not even a nibble.

22:57.120 --> 22:59.739
And if we see something,
we'll just close the door, okay?

22:59.806 --> 23:00.740
